    <detaileddescription>
<para>Contains classes related to loging. Currently logging is implemented in <ref refid="structasmjit_1_1BaseLogger" kindref="compound">asmjit::BaseLogger</ref> class. The function asmjit::BaseLogger::log() can be overridden to redirect logging into any user-defined stream.</para><para>To log your assembler output to FILE stream use this code:</para><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Create<sp/>assembler</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>Assembler<sp/>a;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Create<sp/>and<sp/>set<sp/>file<sp/>based<sp/>logger</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>FileLogger<sp/>logger(stderr);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>a.setLogger(&amp;logger);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para><para>You can see that logging goes through <computeroutput>Assembler</computeroutput>. If you are using <computeroutput>Compiler</computeroutput> and you want to log messages in correct assembler order, you should look at Compiler::comment() method. It allows you to insert text message into items stream so the <computeroutput>Compiler</computeroutput> is able to send messages to Assembler in correct order.</para><para><simplesect kind="see"><para><computeroutput><ref refid="structasmjit_1_1BaseLogger" kindref="compound">asmjit::BaseLogger</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="structasmjit_1_1FileLogger" kindref="compound">asmjit::FileLogger</ref></computeroutput>. </para></simplesect>
</para>    </detaileddescription>
